<item>
            <title>[SPR-7192] Support implicit autowiring for components with single non-default constructor</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7192</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Example from Chris&apos;s DIStyles presentation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AnnotationConfigApplicationContext context = new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext(TellerUI.class, InMemoryAccountRepository.class, TransferServiceImpl.class, FlatFeePolicy.class);&lt;br/&gt;
TransferService transferService = context.getBean(TransferService.class);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This works fine now if all the types have explicitly @Autowired constructors, it would be great if those components could just be autowirable (implicitly).  All we would need would be to optimistically register a bean definition for any class where we don&apos;t find explicit @Autowired instructions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
